                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout>
                           <p>Columns: 3 3;
                                                  ruled lines: 32 32;
                                                  written lines: 31 31; Uniform
                                        layout. Ruled by hard-point on hair-side, last leaves
                                        ruled with pencil on each side. Larger square initial
                                        words. Pentateuch written in three columns, last
                                        pages with Targum around the main text.Masorah magna
                                        in two lines at the top and three lines at the bottom of the
                                        page.Three
                                            kinds of section distinguished throughout the
                                            manuscript: סדורות, סתומות, פתוחות. The letters ס פ are
                                            often omitted or placed contrary to the masoretic rules
                                                ().Masorah magna occupies
                                            two lines of the upper margin and three lines of the
                                            lower margin.</p>
                        </layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <scriptDesc>
                     <scriptNote>Ashkenazi script, square for the main text, semi-cursive and
                                partially cursive for targum and commentaries, of 12th to 13th
                                century.  Ashkenazi square script, probably of 12 or 13th
                                    century. Ashkenazi square and semi-cursive handwriting, probably of
                                    13th century.</scriptNote>
                  </scriptDesc>
